The paper discusses the application of artificial intelligence techniques to prevent security vulnerabilities, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically mentions the use of machine learning (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The paper also discusses the analysis of software specifications (cs.SE) and the use of neural fuzz testing (cs.LG) to detect vulnerabilities. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of careful system development to reduce vulnerability risks, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SI).
